records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jonathan M Miller in court with attorney Michael J Steinle.  Sara Nicole Volden Sadowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for plea and sentencing hearing. Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.  Additional statements by M.M. & S.T.  

AS TO COUNT 1:
The court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, with credit for 1 DAY time served.  

Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 9 MONTHS.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time (as to COUNT 1), STAYED pending review;
-All programming already completed can be applied to probation;
-Batterers Intervention program;
-Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment;
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment;
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent;
-Absolute sobriety;
-NO VIOLENT CONTACT with M.M.;
-Obtain/maintain employment;
-No contact with firearms;
-Provide DNA sample;
-Pay all supervision fees, court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA surcharge during period of probation.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.

Defendant to report to probation intake and provide DNA sample by 4/13/2022.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.

Agent to request probation review hearing with the Court, if it is needed.
